  "text": "The CIFAR-10 dataset consists of 60000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6000 images per class. There are 50000 training images and 10000 test images. We use the common data augmentation process that randomly crop 32x32 patches from padded images of size 40x40 and apply random horizontal flips for training. All models use the SGD optimizer with momentum rate set to 0.9 and weight decay set to 0.0005. We start with a learning rate of 0.1 and train the models for 300 epochs, reducing the learning rate at [CITATION_1] .",
